k |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lMXBQJwyNRgC&lpg=PA79&pg=PA79 |title=Hispanic and Luso-Brazilian Detective Fiction: Essays on the Genero Negro Tradition |chapter='A World Beyond': The Lola Van Guardia Trilogy |first=Jacky |last=Collins |publisher=[[McFarland & Company]] |isbn=9780786424269 |pages=79\u201390 |date=6 March 2006 |access-date=26 August 2018 |via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2004 she published ''No me llames cari\u00f1o'' (Egales), that received the Shangay Prize for the best novel of the year.<ref name=Quiles>{{Cite web |url=http://www.felgtb.org/temas/politicas-lesbicas/noticias/i/392/222/iii-premios-jennifer-quiles  |title=III Premios Jennifer Quiles |trans-title=3rd Jennifer Quiles Awards |publisher=[[Federaci\u00f3n Estatal de Lesbianas, Gays, Transexuales y Bisexuales]] |language=Spanish |date=1 April 2011 |access-date=26 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006 ''Las razones de Jo'' (Lumen) was described as \"an unusual, funny, and irreverent version of ''Little Women''.\"\n\nIn 2012 ''Elogio del Happy End'' (Egales) was the winner of the 6th {{ill|Arena Foundation Terenci Moix Award for Gay and Lesbian Narrative|ca|Premi Terenci Moix de Narrativa Gai i L\u00e8sbica Fundaci\u00f3n Arena|lt=Terenci Moix Award for Gay and Lesbian Narrative}}.<ref name=Moix>{{Cite magazine |url=http://www.revistanois.com/2012/09/isabel-franc-gana-el-premio-fundacion-arena/ |title=Isabel Franc gana el Premio Fundaci\u00f3n Arena |trans-title=Isabel Franc Wins the Arena Foundation Award |work=Nois |language=Spanish |date=22 September 2012 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130411173840/http://www.revistanois.com/2012/09/isabel-franc-gana-el-premio-fundacion-arena/ |archive-date=11 April 2013 |url-status=dead |access-date=26 August 2018 |magazine= }}</ref>\n\n===Short stories===\n''Cuentos y f\u00e1bulas de Lola Van Guardia'' (Egales, 2008) is a collection of short stories.\n\n===Collective works===\nFranc's [[collective work]]s include ''Otras Voces'' (Egales, 2002), ''Las chicas con las chicas'' (Egales, 2008), ''Noves dames del crim'' (Llibres del Delicte, 2015), ''\u00c1breme con cuidado'' (Dos Bigotes, 2015), ''Incidente en el sal\u00f3n'' (a parody of [[Natalie Clifford Barney|Natalie Barney]]'s famous salon in the Parisian [[Rive Gauche]] in the 1920s), and ''Donde no puedas amar no te demores'' (Egales 2016).\n\n===Graphic novels===\nIn 2010 she published, along with the cartoonist {{ill|Susanna Mart\u00edn|es}}, ''Alicia en un mundo real'' (Norma c\u00f3mic), a graphic novel about breast cancer, not without its irony, which received the 2011 Jennifer Quiles Award.<ref name=Quiles/>\n\nIn 2014, again in collaboration with Susanna Mart\u00edn and Norma c\u00f3mic, Franc published ''Sansamba'', another graphic novel with autobiographical touches, a reflection on cultural and emotional boundaries based on a supposedly impossible friendship.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2015/09/25/fotorrelato/1443198512_710406.html#foto_gal_8 |title=P\u00e1ginas plagadas de hero\u00ednas |trans-title=Pages Plagued By Heroines |work=[[El Pa\u00eds]] Semanal |page=8 |language=Spanish |date=25 September 2015 |access-date=26 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Essays===\nFranc's essays include \"Del pozo a la hiena: humor e iron\u00eda en la llamada literatura l\u00e9sbica\" in the collective volume ''Cultura, homosexualidad y homofobia. Vol II Amazonia: retos de visibilidad lesbiana'' (Laertes 2007) and \"Envers un Elogi del happy end\", in ''Accions i reinvencions. Cultures l\u00e9sbiques a la Catalunya del tombant de segle XXI'' (UOC, 2012).\n\nIn 2013 the collective book ''Desconocidas & Fascinantes'' (Egales) compiled minibiographies to bring visibility to silenced women.\n\nIn 2017, Franc coordinated and edited ''Las Humoristas. Ensayo poco serio sobre mujeres y humor'', published by Icaria. In a humorous tone, the book makes a profound reflection upon the presence and absence of women in the field of humor.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eldiario.es/norte/cantabria/cultura/Libreria_La_Voragine-Presentacion-Libro-Humoristas-Ensayo_0_629237325.html |title=Tumbando la falacia de que las mujeres no tienen humor |trans-title=Toppling the Fallacy that Women Do Not Have Humor |first=Rub\u00e9n |last=Alonso |work=[[Eldiario.es]] |language=Spanish |date=3 April 2017 |access-date=26 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Translation and editing===\nShe translated ''El jard\u00edn de Shahrzad'' (Egales, 2008) and edited and prefaced the new version of ''[[Ladies Almanack]]'' by [[Djuna Barnes]] (Egales, 2008).<ref name=Quiles/>\n\n===Theater===\nFranc participated in the theatrical production ''Yo soy Gloria Fuertes'' by Gloria Bosch, directed by Ariadna Mart\u00ed de Puig.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.acec-web.org/spa/article.asp?ID=2573 |title=Yo soy Gloria Fuertes |publisher=Asociaci\u00f3n Colegial de Escritores de Catalu\u00f1a |language=Spanish |date=20 February 2018 |access-date=26 August 2018}}</ref> She is the author of the play ''De Generacions'', a text for three characters that shows how two generations separated by time understand, live, and express feminism.\n\n==Awards==\n* 1992: {{ill|La sonrisa vertical|es|lt=La Sonrisa Vertical}} Prize finalist<ref name=Sonrisa/>\n* 2004: Shangay Award<ref name=Quiles/>\n* 2011: Jennifer Quiles Award<ref name=Quiles/>\n* 2011: {{ill|Arena Foundation Terenci Moix Award for Gay and Lesbian Narrative|ca|Premi Terenci Moix de Narrativa Gai i L\u00e8sbica Fundaci\u00f3n Arena}}<ref name=Moix/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* ''[http://isabelfranc.blogspot.com/ Una c\u00f3mica de la pluma]'' \u2013 blog by Isabel Franc\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Franc, Isabel}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Spanish novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Spanish women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish educators]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish women writers]]\n